**SUSTAINABLE TECHNOLOGY ADOPTION SCORE: 67/100**

Technology Adoption: 17/25  
Innovation Leadership: 17/25  
Measurable Impact: 14/25  
Future Strategy: 12/15  
Industry Position: 7/10

Summary judgment: Expand Energy (EXE) is a large natural‑gas producer that has developed proprietary clean‑energy and emissions technologies (carbon‑capture, liquid‑air storage, small‑scale LNG/CCNG) and operates measurable sustainability programs (water recycling, leak management, third‑party assurance, OGMP 2.0 participation). Many technologies remain at the IP/pilot/ready‑for‑deployment stage rather than proven at multi‑site commercial scale; however, the company reports concrete operational metrics (2024 water recycling, containment, GHG inventory) and has clear, timebound commitments (net‑zero Scope 1 & 2 by 2035, full RSG portfolio and planned third‑party certifications). That combination places EXE as a solid performer among gas producers on sustainable technology adoption, with clear strengths in proprietary IP, reporting and operational controls — but not yet a sector leader versus major renewables or pure‑play clean‑tech companies. Key evidence and sources are listed below.

Findings and justification by research area

Technology Adoption (score: 17/25)
- What they have implemented
  - Proprietary technology portfolio (in‑house IP) including carbon‑capture (VCCS™), liquid‑air bulk storage/power generation (VPS™) and small‑scale LNG / CCNG (VX™) — all described as company IP / patented technologies intended for deployment in power, industrial and gas‑market uses [Expansion Energy technology summary](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHbHUA_8ZdunZjHPyz91V7QnveSnWrL8X_vxp1E6eJV9HdMgapxywwMQ5144wn0RkmJTMOdV4VSqYWOsbXN8JmAFK2NSz6M1hlwRdwVdBvnvJ3VDQjW7g==).  
  - Large operational water‑management and reuse programs in Northeast Appalachia: moved ~184,000 barrels of produced water into operations within a month of a merger and reports pumping ~25,000–30,000 barrels/day downhole; company‑level recycling >12 million barrels of produced water in 2024 [NE App water program](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHO29_HYUZGrdqRwo3der8DhNSP1Ki7vFzuJaelqyjCC2Bgae86P6bmHiZ6flaxXfKnKuJeU3oqkuFdaq6yzSbE6QokOPbN6_rRKGHy2tMS9BRudZBwxj7cKsrnU50_rX3Ffx50s4bicbJXbUmdxeJa8ewiAtD925oOgThnH37Cf3ay0sCVIpgluupg08lyCW735V0qDpR1Yd9r-GHGzsXY8ZJ8KamfHyo=) [Expand Energy 2024 metrics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF0zAmgGx8JRqCATWZ-GAizQXs06hOy7mT3vE3G1_tn-YV-6-SvHQAgF7ZK1eY6nkb7KZs6USH2sxDuyv_MLyrmx8-XcW1jfCKAps_wGx5ODc5CIhIIZVN8_YWALX8p1gp0C73WmAbp3slRPhYWAKTlZ5Y=).
  - Operations and midstream activities supporting reduced flaring and gas monetization (e.g., Expand Midstream Partners activities and renewables spin‑off strategy) [Expand Midstream & renewables](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE0tkl-vMj234wGggQ5KYC1zBVPk-nMpP4KGYalrcgr00e9DwDkMq9lLtYf3slDcfgEdihnDIDt-y0MQ1xKtP53RlSt-T4kvPDYj6Ac2kf4Ej0KegYWVyQA).
  - Robust operational controls (containment >99% of fluids handled in 2024) and leak detection/repair (LDAR) initiatives [2024 operational metrics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF0zAmgGx8JRqCATWZ-GAizQXs06hOy7mT3vE3G1_tn-YV-6-SvHQAgF7ZK1eY6nkb7KZs6USH2sxDuyv_MLyrmx8-XcW1jfCKAps_wGx5ODc5CIhIIZVN8_YWALX8p1gp0C73WmAbp3slRPhYWAKTlZ5Y=).
- Limits and context
  - Several breakthrough technologies are patented and marketed as deployable, but public evidence of large multi‑site commercial deployments and installed capacity (MW, tCO2/yr captured) for VCCS/VPS/VX is limited in the public summaries — most references indicate development, IP and readiness rather than documented large‑scale commercial rollouts [Expansion Energy tech/IP](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHbHUA_8ZdunZjHPyz91V7QnveSnWrL8X_vxp1E6eJV9HdMgapxywwMQ5144wn0RkmJTMOdV4VSqYWOsbXN8JmAFK2NSz6M1hlwRdwVdBvnvJ3VDQjW7g==) [patents list](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFjkfCdoCwsJCEdIE6cBeVVxOJqi5lAn_99IF0s6RFK87OaV4x1NcFhBrAeKjKGImqLwS1Wq755_Z31kC3goodhPHUXuzqBGP7lQ5qaoY2yZR_fkM8OAFFDZmZi5rByc-Sl_guhdbcOnxogREJ1pett6jyV).
- Rationale for score: Presence of multiple proprietary sustainable technologies + significant operational integration on water management and emissions controls, but limited public evidence of large‑scale commercial deployments of the novel technologies -> 17/25. (Matches “Several innovative technologies deployed with significant operational integration”.) Sources: [Expand Energy sustainability & technologies](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFsc9fMVfGZEBpp-ZmE24HYxbcSwOSwfd4nzkppSWo4MFFSIdYkcpA0k3bKBSr7a0-Wjl2lf9aADj4MKMyO46hNa--nSqIuUfs3qxURFrclzD5DV1LV3c5BgFpPB-Yl9na8mkmb7dCELg3WEkbEsP6OHCA=) [VCCS/VPS/VX details](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHbHUA_8ZdunZjHPyz91V7QnveSnWrL8X_vxp1E6eJV9HdMgapxywwMQ5144wn0RkmJTMOdV4VSqYWOsbXN8JmAFK2NSz6M1hlwRdwVdBvnvJ3VDQjW7g==) [water recycling & containment](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF0zAmgGx8JRqCATWZ-GAizQXs06hOy7mT3vE3G1_tn-YV-6-SvHQAgF7ZK1eY6nkb7KZs6USH2sxDuyv_MLyrmx8-XcW1jfCKAps_wGx5ODc5CIhIIZVN8_YWALX8p1gp0C73WmAbp3slRPhYWAKTlZ5Y=).

Innovation Leadership (score: 17/25)
- Evidence of innovative capability
  - Proprietary, patent‑backed technologies and multiple granted patents (examples: US patents referenced in public summaries: 9,260,018; 9,309,759; 9,316,098) indicating internal R&D and IP generation [patents overview](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFjkfCdoCwsJCEdIE6cBeVVxOJqi5lAn_99IF0s6RFK87OaV4x1NcFhBrAeKjKGImqLwS1Wq755_Z31kC3goodhPHUXuzqBGP7lQ5qaoY2yZR_fkM8OAFFDZmZi5rByc-Sl_guhdbcOnxogREJ1pett6jyV).  
  - R&D and commercialization focus on carbon management (VCCS™), energy storage (VPS™) and modular LNG/CCNG (VX™) — technologies that target decarbonization and system flexibility [technology portfolio](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHbHUA_8ZdunZjHPyz91V7QnveSnWrL8X_vxp1E6eJV9HdMgapxywwMQ5144wn0RkmJTMOdV4VSqYWOsbXN8JmAFK2NSz6M1hlwRdwVdBvnvJ3VDQjW7g==).
  - Partnerships/engagements: third‑party verification relationships (Spirit Environmental limited assurance), participation in the Oil & Gas Methane Partnership (OGMP) 2.0, and collaborations with NGOs, peers and academic institutions to advance emissions accuracy and sustainable solutions [OGMP & assurance](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHAjdtyQk20BvIL4gqEMEuMM_jCfXOAooxC3Phri9C0RoBG1nQgxG1pgmHfCfwtLclO90qRX1fsXZEA5Y-9ge9DZYkNrb6tcxVUm1T8uUbfpo8XrJkfKqmYdyIRAGcBWDk2poAERzhVo3_qU7vBbjo=) [assurance](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHCX3T0w9O1THCmD1nyvBXgFmjbt35MiDyVgydBE3lpO8KhDSFDrFdWS-1GeVaCOWrosuuHRx_tewFUkCTn1xM6yD9g_x5G1WOZmJU6UTgd82gNpDinbQwhuzjPz9qaZrvm9VaT7xv70LPYnE7CiP3fcnRHKpXTMViLfJgbJkscPwrVuU1gWUKqtPVkW4TXLwkD5lJYACbI9Jsc).
