Industry Position (score: 7/10)
- How EXE compares to peers
  - Strengths: Largest independent U.S. natural‑gas producer; proprietary cleantech IP and patents; active reporting, third‑party assurance and participation in industry initiatives (OGMP 2.0); substantial operational sustainability metrics (water recycling, containment) that position EXE ahead of many traditional upstream peers on transparency and tech adoption [company scale & fundamentals](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGwcFMBq4M5NqcJh9TbxSgt7KJ9pnGVHZcopRlSZcHZf9oUutMxvAC3zaVpKOZVoItzlG5mm0uFHxFXblYd1BsCrmIdP42N8TxYizVPC4Iovcao1_odP3oKYy25wON3uXjWVdbEcm4=) [OGMP & assurance](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHAjdtyQk20BvIL4gqEMEuMM_jCfXOAooxC3Phri9C0RoBG1nQgxG1pgmHfCfwtLclO90qRX1fsXZEA5Y-9ge9DZYkNrb6tcxVUm1T8uUbfpo8XrJkfKqmYdyIRAGcBWDk2poAERzhVo3_qU7vBbjo=).
  - Limits vs. renewables and clean‑tech leaders: EXE is not a top renewable developer (e.g., NextEra, Iberdrola) nor a large battery/storage OEM; its breakthrough techs (VPS/VCCS/VX) are promising but not demonstrated at the same commercial scale as leading energy‑storage or carbon‑capture deployments described in the broader market [peer landscape & renewables growth](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEJtc0ucNUVREkni2vVtzlrt1h90Opw65iKmEqYMRcWUhRFKXj34SCS9pISKF1Vwz_f0JgNPw2gDuCQJM1EGq7Hu8G-mZ_aJr3hCL4-jzLLmmHG2fcWv4W7i5OmoB3yxkskeBYXELi1QXQMuGMeUx6j00RmLx8V66aV3DNMDzKPo-GdJDgatfOSuyhllCIB7u8I1LRVBRQ4vg==) [market growth context](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF7nGzuBdb9Kp-HunqBVQQ-yBKW7cfV6WzfyMgjplLRq1actCJhxR3o4aF6g6fzUSkuTce_b-MIQpVnEoO_E8tFOzKdKqClVyiyQ-sHyKiVfvIyQqqv6HDDvkibBLz_jUWvtje4ampO_FvDNNhBO278bsROFFwcHp6qc6IjgjcI8LmGq3dS8YQOND_oH9r_F2-BnQ==).
- Rationale for score: Among top performers in the gas‑producer peer set on sustainable technology and reporting, but not an industry‑wide clean‑tech leader -> 7/10. Sources: [peer comparison and market context](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEJtc0ucNUVREkni2vVtzlrt1h90Opw65iKmEqYMRcWUhRFKXj34SCS9pISKF1Vwz_f0JgNPw2gDuCQJM1EGq7Hu8G-mZ_aJr3hCL4-jzLLmmHG2fcWv4W7i5OmoB3yxkskeBYXELi1QXQMuGMeUx6j00RmLx8V66aV3DNMDzKPo-GdJDgatfOSuyhllCIB7u8I1LRVBRQ4vg==) [renewable market trends](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF7nGzuBdb9Kp-HunqBVQQ-yBKW7cfV6WzfyMgjplLRq1actCJhxR3o4aF6g6fzUSkuTce_b-MIQpVnEoO_E8tFOzKdKqClVyiyQ-sHyKiVfvIyQqqv6HDDvkibBLz_jUWvtje4ampO_FvDNNhBO278bsROFFwcHp6qc6IjgjcI8LmGq3dS8YQOND_oH9r_F2-BnQ==).

Specific recent examples (2022–2025) and metrics (from summaries)
- 2024: Recycled more than 12 million barrels of produced water; contained >99% of fluids handled in 2024 [2024 water & containment](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF0zAmgGx8JRqCATWZ-GAizQXs06hOy7mT3vE3G1_tn-YV-6-SvHQAgF7ZK1eY6nkb7KZs6USH2sxDuyv_MLyrmx8-XcW1jfCKAps_wGx5ODc5CIhIIZVN8_YWALX8p1gp0C73WmAbp3slRPhYWAKTlZ5Y=).  
- 2024: Reported Scope 1 = 1.63M tCO2e; Scope 2 = 0.02M tCO2e; methane intensity 0.02%; Scope 1+2 intensity = 2.6 (company reported) [GHG inventory & intensities](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHAjdtyQk20BvIL4gqEMEuMM_jCfXOAooxC3Phri9C0RoBG1nQgxG1pgmHfCfwtLclO90qRX1fsXZEA5Y-9ge9DZYkNrb6tcxVUm1T8uUbfpo8XrJkfKqmYdyIRAGcBWDk2poAERzhVo3_qU7vBbjo=).  
- Net‑zero Scope 1 & 2 target by 2035; 100% Responsibly Sourced Gas portfolio; plan to certify legacy assets under MiQ and EO100™ by end of 2025 [net‑zero & RSG](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHn4WI8vJMy0CphUo1nC7lRYf9jRiEmNC2xL-Z9vuYdl_bgGgYeFHdG-gjyfQRBglLySffM45SmfK3Sm0wYxNgQYvr4w0eWCb6frLTwBRDj7aE2DSSLzHsSUVRZ0DfR3RinjQbaWj81D-2q6NUyeLRkdl60pWCWPrF7stJ-whcXlXnOGBS42iGB6OvDWzCMJNgbtRhieEkjtBfeUFr3dAI8) [certification timeline](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHAjdtyQk20BvIL4gqEMEuMM_jCfXOAooxC3Phri9C0RoBG1nQgxG1pgmHfCfwtLclO90qRX1fsXZEA5Y-9ge9DZYkNrb6tcxVUm1T8uUbfpo8XrJkfKqmYdyIRAGcBWDk2poAERzhVo3_qU7vBbjo=).  
- Proprietary technologies with granted patents and IP (VCCS™ for CO2 capture and sequestration; VPS™ liquid‑air storage; VX™ small‑scale LNG/CCNG) and examples of assigned patents (e.g., US patents noted in public summaries) [VCCS/VPS/VX](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHbHUA_8ZdunZjHPyz91V7QnveSnWrL8X_vxp1E6eJV9HdMgapxywwMQ5144wn0RkmJTMOdV4VSqYWOsbXN8JmAFK2NSz6M1hlwRdwVdBvnvJ3VDQjW7g==) [patents listing](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFjkfCdoCwsJCEdIE6cBeVVxOJqi5lAn_99IF0s6RFK87OaV4x1NcFhBrAeKjKGImqLwS1Wq755_Z31kC3goodhPHUXuzqBGP7lQ5qaoY2yZR_fkM8OAFFDZmZi5rByc-Sl_guhdbcOnxogREJ1pett6jyV).  
