Caveats and uncertainties
- Much of the evidence for breakthrough techs (VCCS/VPS/VX) in the public summaries points to patents, technology descriptions and “ready‑for‑deployment” claims, but public, independently verified large‑scale commercial rollouts and installed capacities (MW of storage deployed, tCO2/yr permanently sequestered, MW of VPS in operation) were not present in the summaries provided. That limits assigning full marks for scaled technology adoption or industry‑leading impact today [technology/IP status](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHbHUA_8ZdunZjHPyz91V7QnveSnWrL8X_vxp1E6eJV9HdMgapxywwMQ5144wn0RkmJTMOdV4VSqYWOsbXN8JmAFK2NSz6M1hlwRdwVdBvnvJ3VDQjW7g==) [patents](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFjkfCdoCwsJCEdIE6cBeVVxOJqi5lAn_99IF0s6RFK87OaV4x1NcFhBrAeKjKGImqLwS1Wq755_Z31kC3goodhPHUXuzqBGP7lQ5qaoY2yZR_fkM8OAFFDZmZi5rByc-Sl_guhdbcOnxogREJ1pett6jyV).
- Some metrics referenced (e.g., Energy Transfer reductions) appear in the summaries as related examples or partner results and should be interpreted carefully when attributing to Expand Energy’s standalone corporate performance [Energy Transfer example](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFojfIkE-fIR0y5i4-Wfcf2RK_-cnANGmno2GKJBe_DZQsxIktg7_zCWEDUY-oHa4NX8As5-MtmhvCkrjqCcynF3mFl-44yLBNzYtfKNhIVbBXafmgnrDUOEc4nJr4RkZlJE-NAJytD2pXrKMUILmWc-ATPVwR2Yz3Hjt4lAf8e0zP6fgRTYZhRnYmUimAIAXb_NUk=).

